    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.56"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">1<unclear>5</unclear> <del>Neih</del>
                Neihardt Collection</note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">5<del/><add>6</add></fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">CLARENCE E. LEMMON, PASTOR
                    EDWARD COFFMAN, JR., ASSOCIATE
                    MRS. ELIZABETH J. CONNER, SECRETARY
                    
                    DR. JENNIE V. FLEMING, GOLDEN-LINK MISSIONARY
                    VEDA HARRAH, SERVICE-LINK MISSIONARY
                    VERN ROSSMAN, SUSTAINING-LINK MISSIONARY</hi>
                    
                        <lb/>
                    First Christian Church
                        <lb/>
                    <hi rend="caps">ORGANIZED 1832
                        <lb/>
                    SERVING MANY GENERATIONS OF COLLEGE
                        <lb/>
                    AND UNIVERSITY STUDENTS</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    Columbia, Missouri
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>April 29, 1958</dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Route 7</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I hope you did not feel that you were under any obligation with regard to the service which I helped conduct for your good wife. You were very kind to write me as you did and I am turning the check into our church treasury as you have suggested in you<add>r</add> letter.</p>
                
                <p>I am sure those present at the funeral services will long remember the beautiful contribution which you and your family made to the service. It was an unforgettable experience.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>With every good wish I am</salute>
                
                    <salute>Very truly yours</salute>
                    
                    <signed>C.E. Lemmon</signed>
                    
                    <signed>C.E. Lemmon, Pastor</signed>
                    
                    <note>cel:vh</note>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
